{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01FdYQF5sQpdCpxiie5zZBqN","content":"[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"JEM-90\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Amp thread reader — parse thread metadata from JSON files\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Add `src/amp.rs` to scan `~/.local/share/amp/threads/*.json` and parse minimal metadata for each thread:\\\\n\\\\n* `id` (thread ID)\\\\n* `title`\\\\n* `created` (timestamp)\\\\n* message count (`messages.len()`)\\\\n* last message timestamp (derived from messages or file mtime)\\\\n\\\\nProvide `fn read_thread(id) -> Thread` and `fn list_threads() -> Vec<Thread>`. Only parse what we need — don't load full message content.\\\\n\\\\nUnit tests with fixture JSON files.\\\",\\\"projectMilestone\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"d2f17c9a-0039-4861-a5db-b44495d5ec6b\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Phase 5: Amp Integration\\\"},\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://linear.app/squareup/issue/JEM-90\\\",\\\"gitBranchName\\\":\\\"jmawson/jem-90-amp-thread-reader-parse-thread-metadata-from-json-files\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T04:51:10.790Z\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T05:28:16.088Z\\\",\\\"archivedAt\\\":null,\\\"completedAt\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T05:28:16.019Z\\\",\\\"dueDate\\\":null,\\\"slaStartedAt\\\":null,\\\"slaMediumRiskAt\\\":null,\\\"slaHighRiskAt\\\":null,\\\"slaBreachesAt\\\":null,\\\"slaType\\\":\\\"all\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"Done\\\",\\\"labels\\\":[],\\\"attachments\\\":[],\\\"documents\\\":[],\\\"createdBy\\\":\\\"Jeremy Mawson\\\",\\\"createdById\\\":\\\"f265a57f-26ba-4ba6-a014-a1414e9067c4\\\",\\\"assignee\\\":\\\"Jeremy Mawson\\\",\\\"assigneeId\\\":\\\"f265a57f-26ba-4ba6-a014-a1414e9067c4\\\",\\\"project\\\":\\\"ishi\\\",\\\"projectId\\\":\\\"032af957-d258-43a4-9cac-246a45582daa\\\",\\\"team\\\":\\\"Jem\\\",\\\"teamId\\\":\\\"3dddde93-b00c-4573-a596-2475a0f69d3a\\\"}\"}]","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019cff68-de11-759d-8d12-0b9523687e71"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"完了です (かんりょうです — Done)! Here's what I implemented:\n\n**Added 3 functions to `src/amp/thread.rs`:**\n- `read_thread(id)` — reads a single thread by ID from `~/.local/share/amp/threads/`\n- `list_threads()` — scans all `*.json` files in the default threads directory\n- `list_threads_in(dir)` — testable variant that accepts a custom directory; returns threads sorted by last activity (most recent first), skipping invalid files\n\n**Added 6 tests:** sorted ordering, invalid JSON skipping, non-JSON file filtering, empty directory, nonexistent directory error, and usage ledger sort ordering."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":621,"cache_read_input_tokens":67396,"output_tokens":168,"max_tokens":168000,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019cff68-de11-759d-8d12-0b9523687e71"}
